<@U2H61EJSG|summer> uploaded a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/summer/F3YG7U87L/app-debug.apk|app-debug.apk> and commented: <@U0260V1BX> (and anyone else interested!) Here is the latest Gauge build. The data now represents the current 24 hour period: there will be 24 peaks and 24 valleys - peaks representing time spent with the screen on and valleys representing screen off duration (i.e. There will be 1 peak and then 1 valley for each hour). The data points are determined by calculating the percentage of on/off usage over the given hour. For example, if my device’s screen is on for 60 minutes, the peak will be 100% and the valley will be 0%. The colors still change, but they now reflect the device usage over the last hour so that users can detect a change more frequently. Let me know if anything else needs clarification!
